  "prompt": "What universities does CRA International recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "CRA International, commonly known as Charles River Associates, recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, often focusing on institutions with strong programs in economics, finance, business, and related fields. While the specific universities can vary, CRA International tends to have relationships with top-tier schools that are known for producing strong candidates in these areas. This can include Ivy League universities, other prestigious private schools, and leading public universities.\n\nIn terms of majors, CRA International typically looks for candidates with backgrounds in:\n\n1. Economics\n2. Finance\n3. Business Administration\n4. Accounting\n5. Mathematics\n6. Statistics\n7. Engineering (often with a focus on industrial or systems engineering)\n8. Computer Science (especially for roles related to data analysis)\n\nFor specific information, it would be best to check CRA International\u2019s careers page or contact their recruitment department for the most current details, as their recruiting strategies and target universities can change over time.",
